huni:Concept.huni:prov_site_tag: The Find and Connect web resource is for Forgotten Australians, Former Child Migrants and everyone with an interest in the history of out-of-home 'care' in Australia.
huni:Concept.huni:name: Adoption of Children Ordinance 1938 (Cth)
huni:Concept.huni:description: The Adoption of Children Ordinance 1938 was Commonwealth legislation that regulated adoption of children in the ACT for the first time. This Ordinance was repealed by the Adoption of Children Ordinance 1965 (Cth).
